    "Continuous data were summarized as mean ± standard deviation or median (interquartile range), while categorical data were presented as frequencies and percentages.",
    "The correlation between the degrees of disagreement/agreement and the demographic characters was performed using an independent t-test or person correlation coefficient.",
    "All tests were two-tailed, with a significance level set at p < 0.05.",
    "ApprovalApproval of Institutional Review Board (IRB) at Faculty of Medicine, Alexandria University was obtained before starting the study (IRB No: 00012098).",
